column14: Please bring masks to any of our hospitals (Somerville Hospital, Cambridge Hospital or Everett Hospital) to the safety officer desk right inside the entrance. Please provide your name and contact information because we want to thank you. If you are unable to leave your home, we are happy to pick up the items. Please email Julia Saggesse (jsaggese@challiance.org)and we will make arrangements to pick them up. If you would like to mail the masks send them to the Somerville Hospital 236 Highland Ave. Somerville Ma 02143 Attention Mary Cassesso CHA Foundation.
column16: N95s, Surgical Masks, Safety Goggles, Paper Gowns, Home sewn masks using https://www.craftpassion.com/face-mask-sewing-pattern/. We ask that you use cotton such as cotton sheets- two layers of material on the mask, please. Two layers are relatively easy to breathe through and provide about 60% of the protection of a surgical mask. We also ask that you put a "pocket" on the inside of the mask so that we can insert a filter if we are able to find them. It has been suggested that we use vacuum cleaner bag filters so if you can find them as well, we would appreciate those donations.  If you have elastic and prefer to use that instead of ties that is up to you and much appreciated.

N95s, Surgical masks, Face shields, Disposable booties, Gloves, Gowns, Coveralls/bunny suits, Hand sanitizer, Disinfecting wipes, Walkie-talkies/baby monitors
Home-sewn masks using https://www.craftpassion.com/face-mask-sewing-pattern/. We ask that you use cotton such as cotton sheets- two layers of material on the mask, please. Two layers are relatively easy to breathe through and provide about 60% of the protection of a surgical mask. We also ask that you put a "pocket" on the inside of the mask so that we can insert a filter if we are able to find them. It has been suggested that we use vacuum cleaner bag filters so if you can find them as well, we would appreciate those donations.  If you have elastic and prefer to use that instead of ties that is up to you and much appreciated.

column14: While we fully understand that doctors, nurses, etc. need PPE's, there is a group that has been forgotten about, funeral homes. We have to take care of those that pass away from/with Covid-19 which also exposes us to the virus. We also have to work with the families of the deceased who may be unknowingly infected as well. Unfortunately funeral homes are on our own to get these PPE's and due to the available PPE's being sent to hospitals or purchased by hoarders, we have been unable to get the PPE's we need. This is why we are reaching out in hopes you will add us to the list of recipients for your masks. Thank you so much.
